
Multi-Containers: 
web-app, main-app pods are created as containers in the pods, scale up together and scale down together.
=Web-app-C & Main-app-C Scale up <--------> Web-app-C & Main-app-C Scale down
spec:
      containers:
        - name: myapp
          image: alpine:latest
        - name: myapp-1
          image: alpine:latest

Init-Containers: 
Init-containers is basically check the database or backend app is started or not, once db or backend starts - 
init-containers will be down. Main-app starts. We can have many init container to run the process before main application starts.
=Init Containers > Database check > Init-C down > Main app starts 
spec:
      containers:
        - name: myapp
          image: alpine:latest
          command: ['sh', '-c', 'while true; do echo "logging" >> /opt/logs.txt; sleep 1; done']
          volumeMounts:
            - name: data
              mountPath: /opt
      initContainers:
        - name: logshipper
          image: alpine:latest
          # Setting restartPolicy: Always makes this a sidecar container.

Sidecar-Containers: 
sidecar-containers starts before main-app starts, it will be end after main-app end.
Sidecar-C Starts before Main-app-C starts ------> Sidecar-C ends after Main-app-C ends

Volumes mentioned for web-app-C should be transfer to sidecar-C via mount path. Mount path can be different.
spec:
      containers:
        - name: myapp
          image: alpine:latest
          command: ['sh', '-c', 'while true; do echo "logging" >> /opt/logs.txt; sleep 1; done']
          volumeMounts:
            - name: data
              mountPath: /opt
      initContainers:
        - name: logshipper
          image: alpine:latest
          # Setting restartPolicy: Always makes this a sidecar container.
          restartPolicy: Always
          command: ['sh', '-c', 'tail -F /opt/logs.txt']
          volumeMounts:
            - name: data
              mountPath: /opt
      volumes:
        - name: data
          emptyDir: {}
